 can be integrated out.
 However, in the setting of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Canini2009"

\end_inset

, even the best performing online methods generally did not improve in accuracy
 as more data was incorporated.
 These online methods were also less accurate than batch (non-online) MCMC.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Our specific context within personalized medicine is different that of topic
 modeling in that while the model is complex and contains several layers,
 the data can be fully stored in memory at once.
 Thus, while the approach of combining IS with periodic MCMC is not fully
 online and not feasible for topic modeling, it is still a feasible option
 for limited sample sizes in our problem.
 An additional benefit of IS is that, relative to variational Bayes approaches,
 the formulas required to apply IS are simple to derive, and can be easily
 ported to other applications within precision medicine.
