 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

 denote this specific posterior sample.
 Averaging over 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

, we estimate the risk of having aggressive cancer for each subject who's
 latent class is unknown.
 The task of generating 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

 was run across 50 parallel jobs on a x86-based linux cluster.
 All jobs were run simultaneously, with a total elapsed computation time
 of 5 hours and 26 minutes
